Halloween night. Well, Halloween afternoon.
//Then years passed, and Halloween is coming again in a few days.

You lie in your bed and look at the bedroom ceiling. The Halloween experience three years ago comes back to your mind.

You look at the dolphin plushie which you gave the same name as yours, and feel like it is smiling at you.

“What do you think, Del?”

“What I saw in the mirror… What happened in that house, could that be real?”

“Was that my imagination? Or did I find a magical mirror?”

Your parents and friends didn’t believe what you were saying, but your gut told you that what happened was real. You can’t help but care about that house.

More importantly…

“You know, Del, it would be so amazing if I found a magical mirror.”

Like the one in Snow White...

Even if this mirror does not talk to you nor answer your questions, the feeling of discovering a hidden secret excites you.

“I need to go there again this Halloween,” you tell Del.

You want the truth -- is it a magical mirror or not?

“But should I go there with someone else? Or should I go there alone?”

