title: Scene2_2
---
<<NextBackground ImageController "housefar">>
That evening you change into your latest werewolf suit, say goodbye to your parents, and walk out of your house.

Your friends are not here. You want to keep tonight as your secret adventure, so you told them you'll meet up a little later.

“OK, Delphine, don’t worry. Just go up to the old house and take another look. Then you can return to Halloween with your friends.”

You look towards the house at the end of the street, up on the hill.

It looks the same as what it was a few years ago, still hard to find under the night sky. Everyone in the neighborhood ignores this house, but you can’t.

"The truth is in there," you tell yourself.

You walk slowly down the street and up the hill, to the door of the old house.

<<NextBackground ImageController "porch">>
The door is once again before you, battered and chipped.

Yet the hourglass knocker shines, polished and tempting.

