title: House2_1
---
<<NextBackground ImageController "brokenmirror">>
You look around and find the side table from your last visit. The plastic bowl is still there, empty.

You look up and realize that the mirror above the side table is broken, its shards dull and lifeless.

Despair takes you, until you catch sight of a shaft of moonlight shining through a doorway to your left.

You faintly hear someone talking, but can’t make out what they are saying.

“Anyone here?” You ask.

The sound echoes in your ears, as if it were appearing directly in your mind.

You decide to trust your ears, and walk towards the illuminated room.

<<NextBackground ImageController "livingroom">>
You enter the front room.

Fortunately, there are no broken floors, trash, or fallen wood chips here. But it still looks dated.

There's a large carpet in the middle of the room, surrounded by sofas, all dated and out-of-fashion. 

Behind the sofa is a wide dusty window. 

Through it, you can see the street outside. Kids in costumes run up and down, paying the darkened old house no mind.

You turn back to the room and notice a fireplace across from you.

A mirror hangs above it.

You approach excitedly. As you guessed - it’s the mirror.

There is not much dust on the mirror, and it looks cleaner than the other furniture, almost newly bought. But you would never mistake the mirror.

“What are you going to show me this time?”

You think of those close to you, wondering if the mirror knows them too.

